# @param {Integer[][]} grid
# @return {Integer[][]}
def construct_product_matrix(grid)
    n = grid.length
    m = grid[0].length

    # Initialize the product matrix
    p = Array.new(n) { Array.new(m, 1) }

    # Pre-calculate row and column products
    row_products = Array.new(n, 1)
    col_products = Array.new(m, 1)

    # Calculate row products
    (0...n).each do |i|
        (0...m).each do |j|
            row_products[i] = (row_products[i] * grid[i][j]) % 12345
        end
    end

    # Calculate column products
    (0...m).each do |j|
        (0...n).each do |i|
            col_products[j] = (col_products[j] * grid[i][j]) % 12345
        end
    end

    # Fill the product matrix
    (0...n).each do |i|
        (0...m).each do |j|
            # Exclude the current element from the product
            p[i][j] = (row_products[i] * col_products[j] * pow(grid[i][j], 12343, 12345)) % 12345
        end
    end

    p
end

# Fast exponentiation in modular arithmetic
def pow(base, exponent, modulus)
    result = 1
    base %= modulus
    while exponent > 0
        result = (result * base) % modulus if exponent.odd?
        exponent >>= 1
        base = (base * base) % modulus
    end
    result
end
